                            <comment id="12941978" author="pmouawad" created="Fri, 8 Jan 2010 10:59:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;br/&gt;
I attached 3 files that enable repdrocing the OOM due to Advisory messages.&lt;br/&gt;
I think that issue is due to the fact that advisory messages are generating FULL Advisory either due to error in MemoryUsage computation based on parent (as I understant in code).&lt;br/&gt;
Thus when many Full Advisory messages are sent, Advisory end up generating advisory for advisory cascading this and ending with OOM &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12941980" author="pmouawad" created="Fri, 8 Jan 2010 11:03:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi again,&lt;br/&gt;
I attached a configuration workaround that solves OOM by disabling Advisory messages on Advisory messages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Philippe&lt;br/&gt;
